Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.90,0:00:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for 35 years, worked in the fields of psychoanalysis, nutrition, and its relationship to brain chemistry.\NFor the last 10 years, I've been doing research into the nature of consciousness itself and its relationship to that which the world calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.02,0:00:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Our subject for today in today's talk is spiritual first aid, perhaps better, how to prevent the need for spiritual first aid.\NSo we will be talking about various principles, things we've discovered through our own research,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.58,0:00:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are perhaps not generally known and we feel should be of great importance to those who are involved in spiritual work,\Nincluding the idea of spiritual first aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.89,0:00:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get started.\NThe spiritual aspects of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.53,0:01:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In this series, we've talked about the relationship between body, mind, and spirit,\Nthat the body reflects what the mind believes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.71,0:01:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind in turn reflecting that which is held in spirit, that which is held in consciousness.\NAnd in this series, we've talked about handling man's problems directly within the area in which they are experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.62,0:01:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is within consciousness.\NIn this series, we've talked about handling man's problems directly within the area in which they are experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.52,0:01:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is within consciousness itself.\NFor as we have said, the body is experienced in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.10,0:01:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no way to experience itself.\NMind itself does not experience itself, but is experienced in a greater energy field called consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.74,0:01:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we will be looking at this directly today in talking about spiritual first aid.\NIn this series, we'll be talking about how to create a safe context from which to approach one's spiritual first aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.49,0:02:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll also be talking about psychological work, a concept that is not prevalent.\NAnd you'll notice for the last ten years, I said I've been doing research into the nature of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.81,0:02:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as director of the Institute for Spiritual Research.\NSpiritual research itself is not a common thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.20,0:02:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've had to learn a great deal because much of what we'll be talking about, frankly,\Nhas not been written anywhere that I've run across.
