Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.89,0:21:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is outside of myself.\NIt will have to be told to me by somebody, because my energy is so low, and the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that my energy fields are all in a negative direction, that I would not be able to find\Nout the truth for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.94,0:21:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the acceptance, the re-owning of the power within yourself, and therefore the\Nworld begins to be experienced, your search now starts to get harmonious, and the God
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.06,0:22:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of that energy field, then, would be a merciful God, merciful, who is accepting, and in that\Nre-owning your own power, in other words, God is pleased, God would be viewed as having
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.06,0:22:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a positive attitude towards your spiritual search.\NFrom that you can move up to the field of lovingness itself, which calibrates at five
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hundred in a very, very positive direction, and that which is nurturing, and supporting,\Nand forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.48,0:22:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, as you move into the desire to be a loving person, the inner healings begin\Nto take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.92,0:22:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to experience life as loving, despite its emotional ups and downs, the process of\Nlife itself, the innate nature of what is going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.74,0:23:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is loving and we move in then to a god of unconditional love unconditional lovingness\Nthe discovery of this is leading into an inner joyful state we begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.52,0:23:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,interstates periodically of serenity and our orientation becomes compassionate\Nthere's the beginning of a progressive shift in process and consciousness into seeing god as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.16,0:23:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection and incredible beauty and we start moving into the capacity to seek on in from the\Nviewpoint of oneness and unity as we move up towards 600 we're moving towards levels which
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.20,0:23:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the world calls enlightened we could say that that below that is called the small self the self with\Na small s and what the world calls ego what common consciousness refers to as i or me because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.99,0:23:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,identified as in the slower state of spiritual life or in the more modern state of consciousness\Nidentifying with these various energy fields and the kind of behavior that comes out of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.91,0:23:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\NAs that identification is let go of, as one's points of view become let go of and become
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.19,0:24:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,further and more and more expansive in one's context of experience enlarges, one moves\Nup towards the top of the box, which we said calibrates at about 600, to states of, which
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.55,0:24:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,generically you might call bliss, states of infinite joyfulness, the experience of\Nan infinite presence, the letting go of the identification with the small self, moving
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.83,0:24:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,toward enlightenment, states of illumination, experiencing God and the world as oneness\Nand God as beingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.75,0:24:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that are the enlightened states, over 600.\NAnd there we find the great saints.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.13,0:24:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The great saints.\NThe great saints.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.33,0:24:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The great teachers of mankind, the great enlightened beings.\NStarting around 750, we find the avatars, the great ones, and their energy fields become
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.51,0:25:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,discernible at that level and then go all the way on to infinity.\NAt least we have now an idea of which way is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.14,0:25:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God is this way, and that which is not God is this way.\NI think it's rather clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.38,0:25:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This may seem simple to us as we look at it, it's common sense, it's something that\Nwe all know within us, we intuitively all know this, and yet how much of the teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.35,0:25:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world is contrary to what appears to be factual in our research on the nature of\Nconsciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.50,0:25:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll be coming back to this now that we have an orientation to the field.\NThat which is truthful, then, carries greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.06,0:25:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at a higher number, it is a higher frequency.\NAnd in physics we know, the higher the frequency, the greater the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.14,0:26:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Electrical power, for instance, is not transmitted across the countryside at 120 volts.\NIt's transmitted at 30,000 volts or even higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.76,0:26:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher the frequency, the greater the power.\NSo we know now why the great teachers, their words have transformed mankind for thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.16,0:26:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of years.\NTheir words are still active, still transforming the consciousness of mankind, thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.46,0:26:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,years after their body has left the planet.\NIt's because of the power, then, we calibrate the energy fields of their words, and we see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.25,0:26:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they are of enormous power.\NSo it isn't what is said, it is the power of the being who states them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.13,0:26:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,At least we have a field of reference with which to now begin our approach, because we\Ndiscovered that there is really no...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.33,0:26:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no safe context or orientation created for people approaching this field.\NThe way to avoid spiritual crises and the need for spiritual first aid later is to back
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.01,0:27:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,up perhaps a bit and do some individual research.\NThe first question, then, that we ask about any teaching is, what is the level of the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.08,0:27:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching?\NWhat is the level of the teaching?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.92,0:27:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because the child within us continues to be naive.\NNaive and innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.52,0:27:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocence, on the other hand, is what leads us into error, because the innocent\Nmind of the child has no means of discernment.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.44,0:27:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we need some way of discernment, some way of finding our way into that which is\Ngoing to be beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.32,0:27:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first question we ask ourselves is, what is the level of the teaching that I'm\Nabout to embark on, or that I am already embarked on?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.10,0:27:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or that is in question?\NIt is obvious that if we are involved in a teaching which itself has an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.82,0:28:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in this direction, that negative experiences are almost guaranteed.\NAn energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.24,0:28:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A teaching which has a positive energy field and calibrates of a high level then is going\Nto bring us into a lovingness, which is the best insurance against spiritual catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.80,0:28:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can pick up...\NA teaching, the teacher of that teaching, the books of the teaching, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.64,0:28:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can ask, is it coming out of this level here?\NWe're not saying that it's right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.56,0:28:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just...\NWe want to know where are we, you know, and what...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.15,0:28:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What pew are we?\NIf a teaching is coming out of this, then these are the emotional experiences that we
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.35,0:28:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can expect.\NWe can expect that these are the emotional experiences coming out of a teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.77,0:28:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Based, let's say, on hatred.\NWe find that there are...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.56,0:29:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that there are teachings that God hates you, hates your behavior, hates your\Nimpulses, hates your humanness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.48,0:29:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the God of hatred.\NAnd when we calibrate it, we find that the energy field is in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.44,0:29:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that the numbers are 30 and 40, around in there.\NOut of that we come...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.16,0:29:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a God of hatred.\NSelf-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.00,0:29:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A God who hates and hates mankind.\NThe view of the world that must come out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.12,0:29:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The self-hatred that will come out of that.\NAnd the inner feeling of being destroyed by this teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.66,0:29:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to get into the study of such a pathway, then you will see what is going\Nto come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.96,0:29:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And at least you're going in with your eyes open.\NWe have the teachings, as we said, of existentialism, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.57,0:29:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Which teach...\NWhich teach of man's hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.88,0:30:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We have teachings then based on worshipping of the past.\NIn which there is a great deal of grief and self-pity for what has befallen this group
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.24,0:30:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of people.\NWe have teachings and teachers who are expressing and exploiting primarily this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.82,0:30:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,called fear.\NIn which case the person experiences then a fear of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.39,0:30:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a punitive God.\NSo these teachings are accompanied by fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.22,0:30:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the energy field is in a negative direction.\NIt will engender fear and further fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.56,0:30:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the exploitation of that.\NSo all these fields also have those who are adept at...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.00,0:30:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can sound convincing as they talk about the truth of it.\NThey are almost like politicians in the religious or spiritual world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.34,0:30:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Very adept at...\NAt their convincingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.14,0:30:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet when we ask, you know, what is their energy?\NWhat is the direction of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.20,0:31:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We find that the teaching of fear is negative and destructive.\NAnd we watch them on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.62,0:31:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We turn off the sound.\NWe turn off the sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.74,0:31:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we look at the face and we see what the face is revealing when it's been disconnected\Nfrom the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.60,0:31:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we test it with kinesiology we'll see that people go weak.\NThis indicating...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.10,0:31:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is being taught is not the truth.\NIt would seem from our research that God is not at the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.14,0:31:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact all the teachings that come out of the bottom of the box all indicate the reverse.\NAs we move up into angriness then we will see those positions which promote anger, conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.18,0:31:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred and religious wars because they are competitive positions.\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.12,0:32:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And God is usually championed then as a God of retaliation.\NAnd because it's a polarized position of us being right and you being wrong, it's always
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.88,0:32:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,viewed that God will punish the non-believers.\NAnd so the punishment of the non-believers is usually one of the traditional teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.00,0:32:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we want to know this is we want to know where we are.\NWe want to know where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.78,0:32:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not saying that it's right or wrong.\NBut we do know where we are then.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.28,0:32:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that we are in the energy fields of consciousness.\NWe know we do know how it...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.76,0:32:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We know we calibrate and how it correlates then with those things when which we can verify\Nare truthful.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.46,0:32:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of all this then is to create a safe context, a safe orientation, a safe\Nspace in which to do our spiritual work because in the spiritual work we're going to be committing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.10,0:32:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,our self to certain goals, certain purposes.\NAnd...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.02,0:33:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be bringing up certain things in that process. And very often one cause of\Nspiritual crises is that the person forgets that they have, through their own intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.81,0:33:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,initiated a process and that what they're experiencing now is a result of their having\Nasked the question, their having made the commitment, their having aligned themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.87,0:33:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with the search for the truth, their having defined themselves in a certain way and has\Ngreat power. And when we look at the power of mind, we see how powerful it is. It has
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.58,0:33:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then the power to bring up within your life the very thing you've asked for. So often\Nin the middle of a crisis, what has happened is that the person has forgotten this, that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.11,0:33:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the person has really asked to bring up that which needs to be healed. And therefore, what\Nis occurring in their life is not a mistake. It's not an error. It's exactly what needs
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.57,0:34:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to be brought up to be looked at, to be understood.\NTo be surrendered, to be re-contextualized, to be healed, to be forgiven. And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.05,0:34:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to come from a compassionate view. How can we heal that which comes up in our\Nlife, if we ask for it to come up in our life, unless we're coming from a healing position?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.25,0:34:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, now you see how critically important it is to know what is the energy\Nfield of a given teaching?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.82,0:34:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If it requires forgiveness…\Nteachings of the Christ based on forgiveness, if it requires compassion and understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.24,0:34:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then the teaching will have to be in a positive direction, and it will certainly have to be\N500 and over, because we know that healing begins at 540. That which the world calls
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.64,0:34:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sin is obviously something that requires to be healed, is it not? So we'll need some teaching\Nthen that is in a positive direction and is at least an energy field of 540. To ask
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.57,0:35:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,people to bring up from within themselves into a negative energy field is to bring about\Nwhat? The destruction. And therefore, it is unsafe to go into any spiritual teaching whatsoever
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.63,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that suggests introspection and soul searching and purification, unless the energy field\Nof that teaching itself is positive and at least to 540, that the teacher, the guru,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.88,0:35:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway, whatever. You can see how dangerous it would be. It would be like putting yourself\Non the operating table and letting your abdomen be opened up by a surgeon who doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.20,0:35:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the skill to handle what he's going to discover when he gets there. So we don't allow a second-year\Nmedical student to open up the abdomens on the operating table. We have to have someone
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.30,0:35:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who has the power.\NSo these energy fields are of power. It requires a great deal of power and knowledge to open
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.36,0:36:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,up one's insides and begin to investigate them. So we don't advise introspection and\Nthe beginning of that inner process of purification until you know that the teacher and the teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.84,0:36:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and those around you are in this energy field of at least 540, which you see is nurturing,\Nsupporting, forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's purpose is understanding and to heal through understanding and through compassion.\NThe god of that kind of an energy field would therefore be a god who loves you because healing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.49,0:36:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,only comes about through loving and his love would be unconditional. If we understand the\Nnature of God at all, we realize that that which is godly is unconditional. That which
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.60,0:36:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is conditional and is therefore limited by definition. It could have always been godly\Nor unconditional. It could have always been godly or unconditional. There is a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.82,0:37:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it could hardly be godly. That which is God is beyond all conditions, infinite. So its\Nlove is therefore infinite lovingness and therefore infinitely capable of a healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.92,0:37:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To create a safe context and a safe space for ourself then, it is necessary to know\Nthat we are in a safe space, that the teacher and the teaching is positive in direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.04,0:37:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that its energy fuel is at least 540, that it holds compassion and forgiveness in a very\Nhigh place within the teaching, otherwise it will be unable to heal that which is brought
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.91,0:37:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,forth.\NThe work that I did with my coworker, Glorian Ross, we checked out and calibrated literally
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.70,0:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands, in fact tens of thousands of factors in various teachings and various pathways.\NWe found out
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.60,0:38:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,consistently that those which calibrated the highest and had the highest ratings and\Nwere in a positive direction were all characterized by the absence of teachings of hatred or condemnation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.04,0:38:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in any way. We found that what characterized the great teachers and the great teachings,\Nthose that calibrated at over 600 in a positive direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.88,0:38:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was a great compassion. Coming from an infinite compassion and forgivingness towards one's\Nhumanness. Viewing it as something that needed to be healed. We saw a lack of concern with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.02,0:38:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a person's money or status. We saw that there was no desire to control the person's personal\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.12,0:38:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no make wrong\Nor invalidation of life in any of its aspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.32,0:39:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And how is this so?\NBecause it isn't, for instance, money itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.34,0:39:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way that it's held,\Nnot the events of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.16,0:39:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but one's position about them.\NAnd so the great teachings,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.06,0:39:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which are in a very positive direction,\Nhave to do with basic principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.50,0:39:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do with principles\Nwhich one can experience the truth of within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.70,0:39:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Through one's own inner spiritual work.\NThe creation of a safe space, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.38,0:39:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of teachers who have no ways to exploit,\Nwho have no ways to invalidate,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.96,0:39:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who are therefore themselves examples of their own principles.\NExploitation of the followers for the sake of the movement or the cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.42,0:39:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there is the avoidance of that polarization\Nof us and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.50,0:40:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is a need for us against them.\NThere is a necessity to keep clear the difference between the phenomenal world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.12,0:40:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomenological phenomena,\Nand that which is spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.80,0:40:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we notice that there is no preoccupation\Nwith things in form in the unseen world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.04,0:40:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually basic principles,\Nwhich then express through all the levels of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.96,0:40:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if we may use that term.\NAnd so the great teachers have no interest in influencing your money
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.44,0:40:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or your life decisions, your personal life.\NMany of them actually refuse to answer questions on that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.28,0:40:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, what they exemplify and speak of is the teaching of a principle.\NIt is then left up to the student or the follower
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.92,0:40:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern how to apply that principle in the given situation.\NAnd so there are no make-wrongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.12,0:40:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no make-wrongs.\NThere is only the teaching of a greater context
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.68,0:41:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from which to hold that life experience.\NAnd so we can get a better understanding of this
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.17,0:41:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if we go back to the board\Nand look at how these various things can be held.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.89,0:41:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We take an event in the world, you see,\Nand the event in itself is of no particular significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.89,0:41:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how we hold it.\NIt's the meaning that we project to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.37,0:41:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the significance that we give it.\NIn and of itself, it really has no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.09,0:41:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So meaning is projected onto it by ourself.\NNow, what that meaning will be will depend on our own level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.05,0:41:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of the teaching.\NAnd so let us take money, for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.13,0:41:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is such a source of conflict amongst spiritual seekers,\Nat least in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.08,0:41:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How would money be looked at, then?\NHow would money be looked at, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.84,0:42:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be looked at depending on the energy field of the teaching or the teacher. It could be\Nsomething that you would feel guilty about. It would be something that it is sinful to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.84,0:42:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,have and God will destroy you if you have money and you can hate yourself for having\Nit and the whole process, of course, is a destructive one because it is a negative energy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.36,0:42:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,field with a very low calibration as far as truth. You might say that these numbers indicate\Nthe degree of truth, 600 and over being, moving into what is called absolute truth, the numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.50,0:42:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom having the least truth. We could then move up the energy field and we might\Nmove into this of fear in which having money then would be a frightening thing, worry and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.36,0:42:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety and panic coming out of it. It would be viewed as unspiritual and as we said before,\NGod will punish you about this or it might be the source of hatred and resentment and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.48,0:43:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,grievance and the money then being used by the spiritual group in a competitive way,\Nretaliatory towards others, leading to anger and religious war or money might be then held
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.30,0:43:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from pride in which it is status, so that your money would be a status symbol that God\Nhas given you, you see. The more God loves you, the more money he gives you and this
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.04,0:43:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from an inflated process. We might move up to a higher energy field and we\Nwe might say that the person here now becomes unattached to the money. He is released. It
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.27,0:43:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't run him anymore. It now becomes okay to have money because the God of that energy\Nfield you see is a God of freedom. Whether you have money or not is not something God
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.93,0:43:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is concerned about at all. As we move up, you might even be willing to now see this\Ndifferently and move into acceptance. As you move on up into the energy fields of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.64,0:44:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude is about 540. One might now view this money totally differently. One might\Nview it as a gift from God about which one is grateful, that the money would then be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.01,0:44:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a way, a tool, a way of expressing your compassion and your unconditional lovingness towards\Nthe suffering of the world because the energy field of love nurtures and supports love,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.75,0:44:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,life in all of its reflections.\NThe beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.71,0:44:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of\NThe beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.83,0:44:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of\NRevelation, because there is the release, as we said, in the brain of endorphins, the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.37,0:44:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing of it as loving then, it might be seen then as a loving thing, that money is a way\Nnow to support others. And therefore you see the intention behind it, the way that it is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.65,0:44:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,held would now view this money as a blessing, as a responsibility, as a way of helping others,\Na way of supporting others. So the money then would be used for the benefit
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.03,0:45:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind, not as an egotistical gesture where you get your name on a brass plate that\Nso and so gave this to that organization. But to use that then as a gift, acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.25,0:45:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the source, to acknowledge the source as the love of God and to view it as an expression.\NYou see, as you move towards the top of the field into oneness and perfection, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.23,0:45:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,all things are aspects of God.\NGod being all that is, you begin to see the divinity within all things. And this would
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.64,0:45:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,then apply to everything in your life. So money, instead of being sinful now, would\Nbe a tool that God has given you so that you can express your lovingness in a greater field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.14,0:45:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and help large numbers of mankind.\NIt could then be held from joy in which one would feel an inner gladness that one has
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.31,0:46:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,been given.\NGiven the power, money here being an expression of God's power on earth to bring about the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.23,0:46:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,healing of the inner pain and suffering of mankind. The expression and nurturing of love\Nthen is the desire, coming out of compassion, for the relief of suffering. And so the money
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.17,0:46:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,would then become a tool in which you could help relieve the suffering of the world and\Ncertainly
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.43,0:46:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the great beings have done that. Whatever assets they had were held as gifts from God.\NAnd the gift was then utilized to bring about the increasing knowledge of man and the relief
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.18,0:46:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of suffering that comes about through the progressive increase of man's knowledge of\Nthat which is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.70,0:46:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one is always sex, isn't it?\NSo let's take a look at sex and how sex and the conflicts arising around that are held
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.18,0:47:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,depending upon the energy.\NWe'll see that sex, an event in human life, part of humanness, can be held from the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.64,0:47:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of the box.\NThe energy field, the teaching coming out of this energy field, would then view it as
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.22,0:47:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,negative as associated with sin and suffering for which God, the God of that level, is the\Ngreat destroyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.18,0:47:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole process is one of destruction and self-hatred, self-pity, self-blame, etc.\NThe next one would be that sex and the conflicts arising around that are held depending upon
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.08,0:47:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field, regardless of what that is.\NIt's a hopeless condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.42,0:47:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's sexuality is hopeless and his whole condition is one of despair and loss of energy.\NAnd what do we mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.01,0:47:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We mean aliveness, the capacity to experience the aliveness.\NHere we might view it as sad and regretful that man is an animal, let's say, that which
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.30,0:47:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,views it, views man as a body because at the bottom here we're viewing man, you see,\Nas a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.34,0:47:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequently, the body as a contact with the body.\NSubsequently, the body as an link with the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.44,0:48:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequently, the body as an link with the body.\Nthe line of the truth he is less and less viewed as a body and progressively realizes that he is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.08,0:48:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit but that which views man his body then would condemn it how sad it is that man is such\Nan animal those who are coming out of fear would view sexuality then with worry anxiety and panic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.70,0:48:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole subject is frightening best to deny and just ignore it altogether because the god of that\Nlevel is punitive and would punish you for any sexuality we can move on up now you can see the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.64,0:48:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,various ways the angriness with which it can be held the people people who hate themselves for\Ntheir own sexuality etc and then those who exploit seduction etc the perversions of religion the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.84,0:48:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,occult demon what do we call them satanic societies etc in which the sexuality and the seduction\Nnow is reversed and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.42,0:49:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,expression then becomes an inflated one in which its importance is inflated out of proportion\Nhow would sexuality then be held once we get up to the level of truth these are all negative energy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.87,0:49:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,fields from the level of truth to begin to face and cope and handle what is sexuality\Nyou know in from the whole viewpoint of spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.23,0:49:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to become empowered now to take the opportunity because the god here is one of an open mind\Nand one of freedom the freedom it's okay to explore this because this says here we're not
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.91,0:49:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to any position about it what we're coming from now is the humility you see this\Nis the beginning of humility meaning i really don't know the answer to this one i really don't
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.88,0:49:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'm willing however to begin to look at it now the willingness because it's a positive energy\Nfield says this is a friendly promising and hopeful subject we can look into
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.22,0:50:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,um we've added our own intention now to clear up the subject and we start feeling a certain\Nconfidence that we have the capacity in a harmonious world with a merciful god now to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.94,0:50:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,explore it without being thrown into hellfire we move on up into an energy field of 500 and over\Nand now it's held from the viewpoint of lovingness and gratitude
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.80,0:50:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it is seen now as an expression of nurturance nurturance and support and healingness\Nmaking love in itself is a healing forgiving act people who have argued and fought etc in the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,embrace forgive each other nurture and heal each other re reaffirm each other's worth and value\Nand so now sexuality becomes an expression of love it eventually becomes an expression
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.76,0:50:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of unconditional love it becomes an expression of the joy and the celebration of one's own alive and\Nexistence a gratitude to god for the joy of existence the beginning of transfiguration and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.84,0:51:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation the moving on to bliss and those who then move on to high states of consciousness\Nsee it as an expression of oneness an expression of oneness a way of being
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.69,0:51:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a way of being and a way of joining those two great energies the masculine and the feminine in\Nthe in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.05,0:51:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you see sexuality then, or money, any of these things, the view about them now is\Nonly a view, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.02,0:51:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In none of these instances can we say what is the thing in and of itself.\NWe cannot take it out of the field of understanding which is coming out of this level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.56,0:51:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So when a person or a teaching expresses their attitudes, their beliefs, their opinions,\Nmany of these things we will find out are merely opinions about a thing, they are not
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.54,0:52:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about the thing itself, they are talking about how they hold it.\NAnd how they hold it then is an expression of their level of consciousness, their degree
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.26,0:52:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of awareness of truth.\NThe lower their view, the more negative they will look at any human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.11,0:52:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And all things can be held from a make-wrong, because the bottom of the box is an endless\Nmake-wrong, the invalidation of life in all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.73,0:52:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that work can be viewed as a make-wrong, all man's intentions, all man's impulses,\Nhis biology, his psychology, even his spiritual ambitions, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.23,0:52:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your desire to be a spiritual seeker can be invalidated, because there is sure\Nto be somebody that says, well, you are just coming from a spiritual ego, you are just
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.91,0:52:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,selfish.\NI mean, you just want to realize the truth for your own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.15,0:53:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And so even your spiritual work itself can become invalidated.\NAnd so these are ways of using the truth against the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.25,0:53:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we move out of that?\NWe can move out of it by seeing clearly what we just said, that there is the event in the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.23,0:53:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,world, there is life itself, there is human nature, and that is what it is.\NAnd then there is...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.09,0:53:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a way of being with that, a way of viewing it, how you hold it.\NThat is expressing a level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.83,0:53:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It is still not saying anything about that out there.\NSo what we find is being talked about is one's own level of awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.51,0:53:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing really being said about the world, you see?\NBecause those who are at the very top, the enlightened beings, all say that all is God,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.22,0:53:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that a thing is what it is.\NThat all is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.64,0:53:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They place no construction on it.\NThey give no valuation of right or wrong to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.03,0:54:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They see the sacredness of all of existence, and therefore there is no invalidation.\NIf all is God, then to invalidate any part of it would be invalidating God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.21,0:54:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Man being God's creation, the least of all to invalidate man and his various expressions.\NInstead, what is taught is a principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.12,0:54:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And the principle would lead you to understand that coming out of this just doesn't work.\NSo you find the highest teachers will tell you that if you follow this course, such and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.54,0:54:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,such will happen.\NAnd they leave it up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.36,0:54:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a very good example in our society of such pure teaching is that of Alcoholics\NAnonymous, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.65,0:54:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes no position about whether you drink or not.\NIt doesn't try to close up the liquor industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.31,0:54:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't try to convince you that you should stop drinking.\NBut it says, for those who had a problem, this is what we did, and these were the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.69,0:54:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you continue on drinking, these will be the results.\NBut there's no make wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.71,0:55:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no invalidation.\NIt's not looking for any power.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.25,0:55:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not looking to exploit anybody.\NIt has no possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.09,0:55:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no royalty.\NIt has no government.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.73,0:55:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no buildings.\NIt has no glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.82,0:55:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just pure spiritual principle.\NAnd then that allows...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.44,0:55:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows the individual to have the freedom to see the truth in that for himself and if\Nhe wishes to apply it to his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.82,0:55:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see exemplified there that which is a high teaching.\NAnd that particular organization, when we calibrate it, does come out at 540, as we
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.86,0:55:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,would expect.\NAn energy field which heals would have to be a teaching that is in a positive direction
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.66,0:55:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it calibrates out at least 540.\NAnd they stand, of course, as an example of healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.23,0:55:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The healing there is based on the physical, the mental and the spiritual.\NAnd it's said that no healing from addiction occurs without spiritual growth and development.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.83,0:56:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What has happened in the lives of many people that are considered saints and wrote autobiographies,\Netc., in which this bottom of the box played a big part in their inner experience prior
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.89,0:56:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to their achieving a higher state of awareness.\NWhat happened was the progressive influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.46,0:56:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?\NThe progressive influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.46,0:56:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As they moved, you see, in their research into their inner selves.\NThey finally moved and brought up the very bottom of the box and faced the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.00,0:56:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and now conscious conception of self as that which is ultimately separated from God.\NThe bottom of the box is the ultimate separation from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.64,0:56:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Until finally the agony, the self-hatred of the exquisite sense of sinfulness.\Nthen brought about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.32,0:56:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Brought about not the discovery of God within sin,\Nbut it brought about surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.47,0:57:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened in each and every case was\Nthe agonizing experience of being so far from God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.71,0:57:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,was so agonizing that the person let go.\NIt was the willingness to let go,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.07,0:57:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept God as God.\NAnd what happened then is they moved up
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.46,0:57:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to a situation called surrender.\NSurrender, when we calibrate the energy field of surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.98,0:57:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it is 575.\NSo what happened is the person removed themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.24,0:57:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from a minus 30 energy field.\NThey finally gave up and surrendered to God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.56,0:57:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy field of 575\Nand opened the way to the experience of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.61,0:57:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those who became enlightened\Noften went through,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.81,0:57:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,agonizing periods,\Nagonizing periods,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.35,0:58:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,40 days of facing that which is the utmost negative\Nburied within one's unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.71,0:58:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,owning one's own shadow,\Nlooking at that which the person has held as most hateful
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.17,0:58:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and owning it.\NBut the enlightenment then came about
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.53,0:58:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,through first the owning of it,\Nbut then it was the letting go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.61,0:58:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of that which is\Nthe farthest,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.51,0:58:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the most removed from the truth\Nin those positions that are coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.97,0:58:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the bottom of the box.\NBut it was the letting go of those positions
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.29,0:58:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that come out of the bottom of the box\Nthat led to the realization of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.49,0:58:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings us to then what is the overall\Ngeneral nature of spiritual work itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.01,0:58:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the progressive letting go of positions\Nand moving into an ever enlarging context.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.21,0:58:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say,\Nthat all that is within the box is the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.12,0:59:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All that is within the box is the ego.\NHigh ego states,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.44,0:59:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,lower ego states.\NThe letting go progressively,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.58,0:59:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because these are all representing points of view.\NThe progressive letting go of points of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.68,0:59:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the letting go of judgment,\Nthe letting go of the vanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.84,0:59:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the vanity coming out of here of I know,\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.92,0:59:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The coming to the surrender through humility here\Nof allowing the process of revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.52,0:59:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of I know,\Nit's that the truth becomes revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.74,0:59:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the progressive letting go\Nof these restrictive positions,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.30,0:59:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,all of which block the inner consciousness\Nand awareness of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.77,0:59:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of the truth then is coming out\Nautomatically of an energy field which gets,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.23,1:00:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively higher until finally it reaches a point\Nwhere one is open to the grace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.66,1:00:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings us to another difficulty in spiritual work,\Nwhich brings about crises and conflicts.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.94,1:00:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the use of the term ego\Nin a pejorative, make wrong kind of a way.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.90,1:00:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, people will say,\Nwell, that is only ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.32,1:00:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your whole life has just been ego.\NYour whole life is a nurse or a doctor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.84,1:00:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or a spiritual teacher or a mechanic,\Nwhatever you happen to be doing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.85,1:00:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an ego trip.\NAs we look at this, we'll see from the viewpoint of truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.96,1:00:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no such thing as just ego.\NIt would mean that there is some place where God is not.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.52,1:00:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, all things represent,\Nlet us say all positions represent ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.16,1:00:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but the ego then is superimposed on that which is not ego.\NThere has to be something larger, consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.16,1:01:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And so to safely do spiritual work and avoid crises,\Nit's necessary to reaffirm and look within
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.16,1:01:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and discover one's own innocence.\NIt is really not safe to do spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.16,1:01:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,unless one has a glimpse at that innocence\Nand keeps one eye on it at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.16,1:01:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that innocence then is the gateway back to the truth\Nso that one doesn't get lost in the swirling of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.38,1:01:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what we're going to talk about today.\NWe're going to talk about the spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.06,1:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to talk about the spiritual work.\NWe're going to talk about how the child is re-discovered
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.00,1:01:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it's re-recognized in the swamp.\NAnd how do we see that innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.00,1:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how can we know its presence?\NWe know that enlightened beings say that all are one with God.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.00,1:01:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, that which is intrinsically innocent\Nis within us at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.92,1:01:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In our other talks, we have talked about how to rediscover that\Nand we've said that it can come about as a matter of revelation
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.92,1:01:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or it can come about as a matter of understanding.\NIf we look at the consciousness of the child,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.08,1:02:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And all, everyone agrees on the innocence of the child.\NHis little consciousness is yet, is not devious.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.88,1:02:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't learned to lie.\NIt hasn't learned the value of, the spurious values of judgment and criticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.79,1:02:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So the child is openly trusting and innocent.\NAnd out of his innocence and his trustiness is where he begins to learn that which is not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.21,1:02:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He hears his parents say, we don't play with certain children because they're of the wrong race or creed or color.\NThey belong to the wrong religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.41,1:02:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And so hatred is taught to the child.\NWe, in other words, to be loyal to our family and if you honor and love your mother and your father,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.11,1:02:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the child then has to adopt that teaching.\NAnd so the innocence of the child then is exploited by that which is not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.95,1:02:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And that which is not the truth comes through generation after generation.\NInnocently enough through the parents, and through the grandparents, and through the family members,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.09,1:03:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and through friends and relatives, and through the teachers, and through television, and the storybooks, and the novels.\NAnd so that which is intrinsically innocent begins to take on to itself programs, beliefs, which are not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.16,1:03:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You might compare the consciousness of the child to the hardware of a computer.\NAnd the programming coming in from social consciousness from the world itself as the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.58,1:03:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NYou see that in the computer, the hardware, that which is intrinsically innocent, is uncontaminated by the software.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.02,1:03:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can run any kind of ignorance or negativity or falsehood through a computer, and the computer itself is uncontaminated.\NYou put on the next soft floppy disk, and the computer's capacity is unimpaired.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.14,1:03:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that intrinsic innocence within consciousness itself is unimpaired.\NAnd as we've said in other talks, it is that intrinsic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.62,1:04:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Innocence that is listening to this voice speaking right now.\NIt is the intrinsic innocence of one's consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.50,1:04:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Listening, trying to find the truth, trying to attune itself to what is real in this, what is...\NThat childlike innocence is unchanged throughout our entire life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.66,1:04:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It never leaves us.\NAnd so when we look at what the world calls ego, or what spiritual work calls ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.90,1:04:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of condemning it, we just see that out of innocence, that's what we believe.\NThat's what we believed at that time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.62,1:04:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What we did was appropriate, if that software program was correct.\NSo therefore, we don't ever make a mistake in our spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.49,1:04:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is on purpose.\NOnce we set our intention in achieving an understanding of the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.68,1:04:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in being open to grace so that the truth may be revealed,\Nhowever you wish to hold it in your own mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.04,1:05:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,whichever expression is most appropriate for you.\NThen you must remember that you have asked all that is in error to be brought up for recognition.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.74,1:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right to do that if you realize at the same time your innate innocence.\NThe innocence of what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.78,1:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocence not of you as a person, the innocence of consciousness itself.\NBecause you as a person are merely reflecting that which is universal,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.74,1:05:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is consciousness itself.\NAnd what has gone on then has gone on as a result of the nature of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.78,1:05:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore there's no point in going into personal self-condemnation about it,\Nnor is there, on the opposite side of the coin, going into personal pride about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.90,1:05:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery of the nature of consciousness itself,\Nlooking into the nature of that consciousness through your own introspection,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.50,1:05:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you will realize that everything you've ever believed in your whole life,\Nyou believed it out of your own innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.54,1:05:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see that, you then develop a compassion and understanding,\Nbecause you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.70,1:05:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your compassion now,\Nout of your compassion,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.58,1:06:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how through their own innocence,\Neverybody has come to believe what they believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.98,1:06:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness then to forgive allows you to see into the hearts of others.\NAnd when you see into the hearts of others,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.74,1:06:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,out of your own compassion,\Nyou see over and over again the innocence of the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.74,1:06:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what the age of the body,\Nconsciousness has remained unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.70,1:06:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You still hear the heart.\Nthe heart of the child within the adult, saying, but won't we all, but don't we, and it's the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.93,1:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of the child still speaking. To keep an eye on that and prevent spiritual\Ncrises, it heals them as they come up. The reaffirmation of our innocence, then, never
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.04,1:06:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,buying that anything is just ego. There is no such thing as just ego. Ego, the software,\Nsocial consciousness, the programming has been superimposed on that which is not ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.51,1:07:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is truth itself, consciousness itself. All spiritual crisis, then, comes\Nout of context. It comes out of meaning. It comes out of the way in which a thing is held.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.83,1:07:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think your diet, for instance, is an unspiritual diet, or your lifestyle is an\Nunspiritual lifestyle, or what you do for a living, all of these things are merely reflecting,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.16,1:07:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as we see now, a certain level of consciousness. Those who have reached very high levels of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.98,1:07:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Condemn nothing. They will affirm, however, that certain levels of consciousness will\Nhave consequences. That a certain lifestyle, a lifestyle of selling out, selling out the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.60,1:07:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,truth about yourself, will bring inner pain and grievance. And now it's left up to you\Nwhether you wish to continue to do so or not. But there is no attempt to control you, no
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.72,1:08:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,attempt to control you. Even the use of hell there, the thought of hell, and the hells are\Ndown below here. They are reversed fields. They are not only 30, 50, 75. They are like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.12,1:08:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a minus 30, minus 50, minus 75, down to minus 100. Even those are then held as merely the\Nconsequences that will come about from certain types of behavior. Not as a threat, not something
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.78,1:08:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to frighten or control people with, not holding that as a negative position, but merely saying\Nthat certain behavior is not a threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.70,1:08:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That certain behavior, certain kinds of self condemnation, etc., will bring you into energy\Nfields that you will experience as the hells. Then it's left up to you whether you wish
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.26,1:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue to do that or not. But hell is not then a threat. It would merely be a fact\Nof human consciousness. A fact of human consciousness. That the inner agony can become greater than
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.00,1:09:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is already if you violate certain principles.\NAnd so the teaching still holds up then that it can be a very high teaching even though
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.68,1:09:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it may warn us that very agonizing and painful states of consciousness can come about as\Na result of certain behavior.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.72,1:09:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All experience within human consciousness, that includes of course all of spiritual work,\Nis representing a position. It's representing a way of being with, a way of holding. And
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.60,1:09:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're always talking about then, even though when we think we're talking about\Nthe external world, is really an inner position coming out of a certain level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.04,1:09:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How we are with a thing, how we can choose to be with it. And the pains and the agonies\Nthat come about are coming about as a result of our hanging on to, hanging on to what?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.12,1:09:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hanging on to putting our survival on something that is not the truth. Pain tells us that\Nwe have,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.73,1:10:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've been hanging on to something, that we've put our survival on to something which\Nis a violation of some principle of consciousness. And that really is what spiritual work is about.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.63,1:10:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the progressive pain then of these positions is telling us that they are far from the truth.\NIt isn't that they're wrong. You see, there's no make wrong. It's that as you get closer
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.53,1:10:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and closer to the experience of the presence of God, the inner experience is one of increasing\Njoy and happiness. As we get farther from it, it tells us that we are far removed from
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.17,1:10:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth. Therefore, it's not a make wrong. It's not right or wrong. It's just that it's\Npainful and doesn't work. Coming out of desiringness, for instance, the Buddha said that all pain
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.73,1:10:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffering is based on desiringness. And a greater elaboration of that is that the\Ndesiringness is coming out of a fear, and the fear is coming out of a sense of lack,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.83,1:11:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the\Nbelief that one is separated from God. So he's not saying that you can't desire anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.42,1:11:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just saying that desiringness itself is going to lead to progressive frustration\Nand a feeling of being separated from the truth, and that you're going to be constantly
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.36,1:11:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting and craving, and that you're going to be entrapped by that. There's no right\Nor wrong about it. There's no saying we should go to war with those people. Those people
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.39,1:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have souls, and God hates them and will throw them into hell. No such thing.\NAll he's saying is that the consequences of this endless frustration is going to lead
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.53,1:11:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to anger. If you acquire that which you desire, you're going to go into pridefulness. If you\Ndon't, you're going to fear that you're going to lose it. If you keep trying and don't make
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.23,1:11:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you're going to go into apathy and guilt. So all he's saying is that the consequences\Nare negative. The consequences are not going to support your movement towards the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.78,1:12:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that in these energy fields that one negative level of energy tends to\Nbring forth all of them. So that desiringness doesn't remain pure, it tends to bring with
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.02,1:12:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it anger and pride and fear and grief and apathy. And so grief tends to pull with it\Nfearful, angry, desiringness. And each of these tends to pull the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.56,1:12:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The critical point in all spiritual work then is this capacity to be willing to tell the\Ntruth. Very often that truth is, I don't know. And it's the out of I don't know comes the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.96,1:12:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to be willing to tell the truth. And it's the out of I don't know comes the\Nwillingness to surrender, which is 575, to God. And the truth then comes about through
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.16,1:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an act of surrender. The truth then out of the pain, which leads many people into spiritual\Nwork, is not coming out of the pain. And the mistake is to worship the pain and think that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.00,1:13:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering therefore is the royal road to enlightenment. It's the realization by facing all the suffering\Nwithin oneself that it is not the truth. And it is the willingness to let it go and surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.70,1:13:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it to God that the truth is revealed.\NOur whole position then about our inner innocence, the remembering that when we start spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.63,1:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,work we are asking to have that which is not the truth brought up to our awareness and\Ntherefore it is evidence of success. Therefore the somewhat chaotic appearance of the lives
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.80,1:13:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who are labeled spiritual seekers, many of them their life becomes somewhat chaotic\Nto the outside observer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.40,1:13:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner person is pleased because it says, I've asked to see what stands between me and\Nthe truth and that has been brought up for my awareness to be recognized, re-owned, re-contextualized
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.40,1:13:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and healed.\NHow to come from a safe context then about one's spiritual work? How to provide for yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.89,1:14:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a safe space? To come from the heart, that which is the heart with a capital H, not the\Nphysical heart, but the ultimate compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.43,1:14:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The owning of oneself from this level, the joy of the spiritual work, the saying thank\Nyou to all the things that come up out of gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.43,1:14:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The crisis is the very event of the spiritual healing. It is out of the crisis that the\Nhealing occurs.
